    <title>Pork Tostadas with Salsa Verde</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Pork Tostadas with Salsa Verde</h1>
    <p><strong>Servings:</strong> 2 (double for 4)</p>
    <p><strong>Notes:</strong> If you're cooking for 4 servings, double measurements accordingly.</p>
    
    <h2>Ingredients</h2>
    <ul class="ingredients">
        <li>12 oz Green Cabbage</li>
        <li>7 oz Tomatillo</li>
        <li>1 Jalapeño</li>
        <li>¼ oz Cilantro</li>
        <li>4 oz Red Onion, Diced</li>
        <li>1 tbsp Garlic</li>
        <li>1 tbsp Orange Juice Concentrate</li>
        <li>4 Corn Tortillas</li>
        <li>1 pkg Raw Sugar Pack</li>
        <li>4 tsp Spice Blend (⅛ tsp Ancho Powder, ½ tsp Chili Powder, 2 tsp Oregano, ½ tsp Cumin, ⅛ tsp Cinnamon; spicy ingredient, use with discretion)</li>
        <li>1 Avocado</li>
        <li>½ cup Feta</li>
        <li>1 package Sliced Pork</li>
        <li>Salt & Pepper to taste</li>
        <li>Oil as needed</li>
        <li>¼ cup Water</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2>Instructions</h2>
    <ol class="instructions">
        <li>Prepare Ingredients: Turn broiler to 500°F with rack placed 6 inches from the top. Line a baking sheet with foil. Wash tomatillo, cabbage, jalapeño, and cilantro. Finely dice tomatillo into ¼ inch pieces and place in a medium bowl. Pick and finely chop cilantro leaves and add to bowl with tomatillo. Cut jalapeño in half and remove stem and seeds. Finely chop into ¼ inch pieces. Drain and pat pork dry with paper towel. Wash hands with soapy water.</li>
        <li>Prepare Salsa Verde: To the bowl with tomatillos, add half of each: onions and garlic. Add jalapeño and salt to taste, and stir to combine. Set aside.</li>
        <li>Bake Tostadas: Brush tortillas with a thin layer of oil on both sides. Place tortillas in a single layer on baking sheet. Place tray in oven and broil for 2-4 minutes, flipping halfway, until crisp and golden. Monitor closely to prevent burning.</li>
        <li>Cook Pork: Heat a large non-stick skillet over medium heat. Once hot, add pork, remaining onions, and garlic, and cook for 2-3 minutes, pulling pork apart using tongs. Season well with salt and pepper, and cook until the outside of pork is no longer pink. Add orange juice concentrate, sugar, spice blend, ¼ cup water and cook 3-4 minutes until pork reaches an internal temperature of 165°F and sauce thickens.</li>
        <li>Finish & Assemble: Slice avocado in half and remove pit. Slice into ¼ inch slices and divide among tostadas and gently mash with a fork. Top with tostadas with cabbage. Using tongs, remove pork from sauce and place over cabbage. Top with salsa verde, crumbled feta cheese, and a drizzle of sauce from skillet if desired. Enjoy!</li>
    </ol>
    
    <h2>Equipment</h2>
    <ul class="equipment">
        <li>Baking Sheet</li>
        <li>Foil</li>
        <li>Medium Bowl</li>
        <li>Large Non-Stick Skillet</li>
        <li>Tongs</li>
        <li>Oven/Broiler</li>
    </ul>
</body>
